{"title":"Max and TNT Sports Will Stream Cycling Coverage in the U.S. Starting February 2024","link":"https://bikerumor.com/max-and-tnt-sports-will-stream-cycling-coverage-in-the-us/","date":1702572048000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/MAX-logo-cycling-coverage-streaming-US.jpg\" alt=\"MAX logo cycling coverage streaming US\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/MAX-logo-cycling-coverage-streaming-US.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/MAX-logo-cycling-coverage-streaming-US-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/MAX-logo-cycling-coverage-streaming-US-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/MAX-logo-cycling-coverage-streaming-US-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/MAX-logo-cycling-coverage-streaming-US-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/MAX-logo-cycling-coverage-streaming-US-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/MAX-logo-cycling-coverage-streaming-US-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Max and TNT Sports, a division of Warner Bros. Discovery (the same people that own GCN+), have good news for riders looking for cycling coverage in peak trainer season. Starting February 2024, the Bleacher Report Sports Add-On on ‘Max’ will now provide live cycling coverage spanning road, mountain bike, track, BMX, and cyclocross.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cannondale-SuperSlice-Evo-TT-bike-sneak-peek_prototype-disc-brake-carbon-time-trial-bike-raced-at-Tirreno-Adriatico-by-EF-Pro-Cycling-Sebeastian-Langeveld_screengrab-from-GCNplus.jpg\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cannondale-SuperSlice-Evo-TT-bike-sneak-peek_prototype-disc-brake-carbon-time-trial-bike-raced-at-Tirreno-Adriatico-by-EF-Pro-Cycling-Sebeastian-Langeveld_screengrab-from-GCNplus.jpg\" alt=\"Cannondale SuperSlice Evo TT bike sneak peek, prototype disc brake carbon time trial bike, GCN+ race coverage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cannondale-SuperSlice-Evo-TT-bike-sneak-peek_prototype-disc-brake-carbon-time-trial-bike-raced-at-Tirreno-Adriatico-by-EF-Pro-Cycling-Sebeastian-Langeveld_screengrab-from-GCNplus.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cannondale-SuperSlice-Evo-TT-bike-sneak-peek_prototype-disc-brake-carbon-time-trial-bike-raced-at-Tirreno-Adriatico-by-EF-Pro-Cycling-Sebeastian-Langeveld_screengrab-from-GCNplus-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cannondale-SuperSlice-Evo-TT-bike-sneak-peek_prototype-disc-brake-carbon-time-trial-bike-raced-at-Tirreno-Adriatico-by-EF-Pro-Cycling-Sebeastian-Langeveld_screengrab-from-GCNplus-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cannondale-SuperSlice-Evo-TT-bike-sneak-peek_prototype-disc-brake-carbon-time-trial-bike-raced-at-Tirreno-Adriatico-by-EF-Pro-Cycling-Sebeastian-Langeveld_screengrab-from-GCNplus-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cannondale-SuperSlice-Evo-TT-bike-sneak-peek_prototype-disc-brake-carbon-time-trial-bike-raced-at-Tirreno-Adriatico-by-EF-Pro-Cycling-Sebeastian-Langeveld_screengrab-from-GCNplus-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cannondale-SuperSlice-Evo-TT-bike-sneak-peek_prototype-disc-brake-carbon-time-trial-bike-raced-at-Tirreno-Adriatico-by-EF-Pro-Cycling-Sebeastian-Langeveld_screengrab-from-GCNplus-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cannondale-SuperSlice-Evo-TT-bike-sneak-peek_prototype-disc-brake-carbon-time-trial-bike-raced-at-Tirreno-Adriatico-by-EF-Pro-Cycling-Sebeastian-Langeveld_screengrab-from-GCNplus-400x225.jpg 400w\" /></a><figcaption>race coverage screengrab from GCN+</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Max streaming service will take over where GCN+ drops off, with over 300 premiere cycling events. US viewers can now stream races like the Giro d’Italia, all UCI Mountain Bike World Series race weekends, UCI Track Champions League rounds, 53 women’s World Tour Pro Series broadcasts, the E3 Saxo Bank Classic, the Kuurne–Brussels–Kuurne, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Team-Sky-GCN-3.jpg\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Team-Sky-GCN-3.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Team-Sky-GCN-3.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Team-Sky-GCN-3-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Team-Sky-GCN-3-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Team-Sky-GCN-3-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Team-Sky-GCN-3-600x338.jpg 600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Subscribers can also access “The Breakaway,” offering English-language pre- and post-race coverage. The coverage features insights from cycling experts like two-time Tour de France winner Alberto Contador, former World Road Race champion Philippe Gilbert, 17-year ex-pro and fan favorite Jens Voigt, and 24-time Grand Tour stage winner Robbie McEwen.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information and to subscribe, check out <a href=\"https://bleacherreport.com/\">Bleacherreport.com</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/max-and-tnt-sports-will-stream-cycling-coverage-in-the-us/\">Max and TNT Sports Will Stream Cycling Coverage in the U.S. Starting February 2024</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3581cbb1e18f367b6614ea68b57600cb70391fcce5f1015f2e4eef8a8fcf2206","category":"Cycling"}